### SwipeBuddy API Test Collection
### Install "REST Client" VS Code extension to run these inline.
### Run "1.2 Login" first — the token is auto-captured and reused everywhere.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api/v1
@token = {{login.response.body.data.token}}

### =========================================
### 1. AUTH  (rate-limited: 20 req / 15 min)
### =========================================

### 1.1 Signup
# @name signup
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Aditya Sharma",
  "age": 24,
  "gender": "male",
  "phone": "9876543210",
  "password": "password123"
}

###

### 1.2 Login  ← run this first; token is auto-captured
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phone": "9876553210",
  "password": "pas"
}

###

### 1.3 Login with wrong password (expect 401)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phone": "9876543210",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
}

###

### =========================================
### 2. MASTER LOOKUPS  (all require auth)
### Use these to populate UI dropdowns,
### then send the selected IDs in the
### profile/flat endpoints below.
### =========================================

### 2.1 List all Degrees
GET {{baseUrl}}/master/degrees
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 2.2 List all Positions
GET {{baseUrl}}/master/positions
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 2.3 List all Companies
GET {{baseUrl}}/master/companies
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 2.4 List all Institutions
GET {{baseUrl}}/master/institutions
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 2.5 List all Habits
GET {{baseUrl}}/master/habits
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 2.6 List all Amenities
GET {{baseUrl}}/master/amenities
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### =========================================
### 3. PROFILE  (auth required)
### =========================================

### 3.1 Get my own profile (includes jobs, education, habits)
GET {{baseUrl}}/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 3.2 Update my profile (all fields optional — send only what changes)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Aditya Sharma",
  "age": 24,
  "gender": "male",
  "city": "Bengaluru",
  "state": "Karnataka",
  "search_type": "flat",
  "is_published": true
}

###

### 3.3 View another user's public profile (no auth needed)
# Replace the UUID below with a real user id
GET {{baseUrl}}/profile/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

###

### =========================================
### 4. PROFILE → JOBS  (auth required)
### company_id / position_id come from
### GET /master/companies & /master/positions
### =========================================

### 4.1 Get my jobs
GET {{baseUrl}}/profile/jobs
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 4.2 Add a job experience
# @name addJob
POST {{baseUrl}}/profile/jobs
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "company_name": "Google",
  "position_name": "SDE",
  "from_year": "2022",
  "till_year": "2024",
  "currently_working": false,
  "display_order": 1
}

###

### 4.2b Add job with master IDs (preferred when company/position exist in master)
POST {{baseUrl}}/profile/jobs
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "company_id": "REPLACE_WITH_COMPANY_UUID",
  "position_id": "REPLACE_WITH_POSITION_UUID",
  "from_year": "2022",
  "till_year": "2024",
  "currently_working": false,
  "display_order": 1
}

###

### 4.3 Update a job experience
# Replace :jobId with the id from addJob response
PUT {{baseUrl}}/profile/jobs/{{addJob.response.body.data.id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "currently_working": true,
  "till_year": null
}

###

### 4.4 Soft-delete a job experience
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/profile/jobs/{{addJob.response.body.data.id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### =========================================
### 5. PROFILE → EDUCATION  (auth required)
### institution_id / degree_id come from
### GET /master/institutions & /master/degrees
### =========================================

### 5.1 Get my education
GET {{baseUrl}}/profile/education
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 5.2 Add an education entry
# @name addEdu
POST {{baseUrl}}/profile/education
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "institution_name": "IIT Delhi",
  "degree_name": "B.Tech",
  "start_year": "2018",
  "end_year": "2022",
  "display_order": 1
}

###

### 5.2b Add education with master IDs (preferred when institution/degree exist in master)
POST {{baseUrl}}/profile/education
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "institution_id": "REPLACE_WITH_INSTITUTION_UUID",
  "degree_id": "REPLACE_WITH_DEGREE_UUID",
  "start_year": "2018",
  "end_year": "2022",
  "display_order": 1
}

###

### 5.3 Update an education entry
PUT {{baseUrl}}/profile/education/{{addEdu.response.body.data.id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "end_year": "2023"
}

###

### 5.4 Soft-delete an education entry
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/profile/education/{{addEdu.response.body.data.id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### =========================================
### 6. PROFILE → MY HABITS  (auth required)
### habit_ids come from GET /master/habits
### This REPLACES all existing habits in one call.
### Send [] to clear all habits.
### =========================================

### 6.1 Get my current habits
GET {{baseUrl}}/profile/habits
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 6.2 Replace my habits (send array of habit UUIDs)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/profile/habits
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "habit_ids": []
}

###

### =========================================
### 7. PROFILE → LOOKING-FOR HABITS  (auth required)
### Preferred lifestyle habits in a flatmate.
### habit_ids come from GET /master/habits
### =========================================

### 7.1 Get my looking-for preferences
GET {{baseUrl}}/profile/looking-for
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 7.2 Replace looking-for habits
PUT {{baseUrl}}/profile/looking-for
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "habit_ids": []
}

###

### =========================================
### 8. FLATS
### GET /flats and GET /flats/:id → public
### POST /flats → auth required
### user_id is auto-injected from JWT
### =========================================

### 8.1 List all published flats (no auth required)
GET {{baseUrl}}/flats

###

### 8.2 Create a flat (auth required)
# @name createFlat
POST {{baseUrl}}/flats
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "address": "123 Startup Avenue",
  "city": "Bengaluru",
  "state": "Karnataka",
  "pincode": "560001",
  "latitude": 12.9716,
  "longitude": 77.5946,
  "furnishing_type": "furnished",
  "description": "Awesome 3BHK to share",
  "is_published": true
}

###

### 8.3 Get flat by ID (no auth required)
GET {{baseUrl}}/flats/{{createFlat.response.body.data.id}}

###

### 8.4 Create flat without required fields — expect 500 (validation error)
POST {{baseUrl}}/flats
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "city": "Bengaluru"
}

###

### 8.5 Create flat without token — expect 401
POST {{baseUrl}}/flats
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "address": "123 MG Road",
  "city": "Bengaluru",
  "state": "Karnataka"
}

###

### =========================================
### 9. MATCHING  (auth required — stub)
### =========================================

### 9.1 Discover profiles/flats
GET {{baseUrl}}/matching
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 9.2 Swipe on a profile or flat
POST {{baseUrl}}/matching/swipe
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

###

### 9.3 Matching without token — expect 401
GET {{baseUrl}}/matching

###

### =========================================
### 10. MESSAGING  (auth required — stub)
### =========================================

### 10.1 List all conversations
GET {{baseUrl}}/messages
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 10.2 Get messages for a conversation
GET {{baseUrl}}/messages/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 10.3 Messaging without token — expect 401
GET {{baseUrl}}/messages

###

### =========================================
### 11. SOCIAL  (auth required — stub)
### =========================================

### 11.1 Get saved/bookmarked profiles
GET {{baseUrl}}/social/saved-profiles
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 11.2 Report a user
POST {{baseUrl}}/social/reports
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

###

### 11.3 Get blocked users
GET {{baseUrl}}/social/blocks
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 11.4 Social without token — expect 401
GET {{baseUrl}}/social/saved-profiles

###
